	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103723446244972><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=16355&mid=103723446244972>Aztec/Mayan History?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=16355&mid=103723446244972#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97774><span id= >moruti</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 13th 8:02 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If memory serves me correctly, it was mentioned in one of my Pre-Colombian Spanish classes about the history of these *chipotles* in Mayan/Aztec history.&nbsp;&nbsp;Apparently there were some victims who were up to be a sacrifice.  They were given the choice of either serving as a blood sacrifice, by having their hearts removed, or they could eat a bowl of these peppers.  There were not any cases of any victim ever choosing the peppers.<br>&nbsp;<br>Lasciate ogne 'speranza<br>Voi ch' intrate<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  -Dante</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
